## Code Organization
- Place code in correct directories: `js/core/` (shared logic), `js/tools/` (UI features), `js/utils/` (helpers), `src/transformers/` (transform logic)
- Extract utilities to `js/utils/` when reused
- Use `js/config/constants.js` for magic numbers (UPPER_SNAKE_CASE)

## Security
- Never use `eval()` - use `window.EscapeParser.parseEscapeSequence()` instead
- Validate and sanitize user inputs
- Avoid exposing sensitive data in logs/frontend

## Code Style
- Use ES6+ (arrow functions, const/let, template literals)
- Add JSDoc comments for public functions
- Follow existing file naming: `camelCase.js` for tools/utils, `kebab-case.js` for transformers
- Classes: `PascalCase`, Functions: `camelCase`, Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`

## Transformers
- Inherit from `BaseTransformer.js`
- Place in appropriate category directory (`ciphers/`, `base-encodings/`, etc.)
- Run `npm run build` after changes
- Update tests in `tests/test_universal.js`
- Update documentation if needed

## Tools (UI Features)
- Extend `Tool` base class from `js/tools/Tool.js`
- Register in `js/tools/index.js`
- Add script tag to `index.html` before `app.js`
- Keep Vue data/methods/template in tool class

## Testing & Build
- Run `npm test` before submitting
- Run `npm run build` after transformer changes
- Test in browser (open `index.html`)
- Ensure no console errors

## Documentation
- Update relevant docs when adding features
- Add JSDoc for new public functions
- Update `CONTRIBUTING.md` if adding new patterns

